{
  "stem": "19690.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He brought out a book that was written or compiled, rather, by Klaus [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was a-- it was a copy of all the teletypes that were sent from Paris to Berlin indicating the transports and who was on them.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He said, here, look through this book.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Do you have an idea when?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I said, well, they left Le Milles on the 13th of August, probably about the 17th-- which was my birthday, by the way.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] When we opened up the book, there were pages-- each train contained 1,000 passengers.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And every name and birth date and home town of these people were listed.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "On the 17th was the day my parents left for Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] It was in black and white on those sheets.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I looked further and I found my Aunt Ruth and Uncle Ernst left there in September and so did my Uncle Henry, Aunt Elsa, and cousin Martin.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He was not exempt because he was over 16.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the destination of all of them was Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I never heard from my parents again.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I did get a postcard while we were in-- while I was in Switzerland for my Uncle Ernst, which I have here, which told me that he was separated from his wife and that he was working in Silesia, southern Poland.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it was all written in the third person and that he would write again.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He was writing as he was his friend and that he would write again.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But we never heard anymore from him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He was the youngest of the men, in the best physical shape, and he apparently lasted the longest.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I stayed in Switzerland, to get back to that, until after the war.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
